Trunk Based Development

Very popular in companies like Google.

Layman Explanation

Instead of many branches, everyone works on one main branch called trunk.

Developers create very small short-lived branches and merge them quickly.

Diagram
trunk (main)
   |
   |-- small feature branch -- merge
   |
   |-- small bug fix --------- merge
   |
   |-- small improvement ----- merge


Branches usually live less than 1–2 days.

Workflow

1️⃣ Developers create a small branch.
feature-small-change

2️⃣ Commit quickly.

3️⃣ Merge into trunk immediately.

4️⃣ CI runs automated tests.

Interview Answer

Trunk Based Development is a branching strategy where developers frequently merge small changes into a single shared branch (trunk), enabling continuous integration and faster releases.

Advantages

Very fast development

Supports continuous integration

Minimal merge conflicts

Disadvantages

Requires strong automated testing

Requires disciplined developers
